parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The seat belt cable comes off the track
the seat belt is stuck or frozen in a midway position
the cable that moves the shoulder restraint back and forth comes out of its track
the seat belt warning light illuminates intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the motorized seat belt can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to operate
the seat belt warning light illuminates
the seat belt is stuck or frozen in a midway position

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt warning system can cause the driver to be unaware of an inoperable seat belt, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The seat belt warning light illuminates intermittently
the seat belt warning bell goes off and on continuously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to unexpected loss of power to critical systems, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ignition switch fails to turn
the wipers and blower functions are lost
the steering column starts to smoke
the car horn malfunctions or blows by itself.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause unexpected loss of power to critical systems, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The wipers and blower functions are lost
the steering column starts to smoke
the car horn malfunctions or blows by itself
the battery needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical short in the steering column can cause a fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Smoke comes from the steering column area
the steering column starts to smoke.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A ruptured or corroded fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, or other hazardous situations, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers.
A corroded or failed fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
A failed fuel filter can cause the vehicle to jerk or cut off, leading to loss of control, accidents, or other safety risks.
A failed gas intake valve can cause engine performance issues, stalling, or failure, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
